<h2 id="motivation">Motivation</h2>

<p>I want to use spark via both python and scala with Jupyter notebook without having to import all those modules associated with pyspark. Iâ€™m using Windows.</p>

<h2 id="preparation">Preparation</h2>

<p>This post assumes configurations <a href="https://largecats.github.io/2019/07/31/install-spark-on-windows/">here</a> and <a href="https://largecats.github.io/2019/07/31/set-up-pyspark-with-jupyter-notebook/">here</a>.</p>

<h2 id="method">Method</h2>

<p>I tried a number of kernels in <a href="https://github.com/jupyter/jupyter/wiki/Jupyter-kernels">this list</a>, only <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">spylon-spark</code> seems to work.</p>

<p>Follow the instructions <a href="https://github.com/Valassis-Digital-Media/spylon-kernel">here</a>.</p>

